    "steps": [
      "Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C) and line a baking sheet with parchment paper.",
      "In a medium bowl, toss the chopped almonds and pepitas with the tamari, maple syrup, and smoked paprika until well coated. Spread them evenly on the prepared baking sheet.",
      "Bake for 10 to 14 minutes, stirring halfway, until golden brown. Remove from the oven and let cool completely.",
      "In a large bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, olive oil, apple cider vinegar, Dijon mustard, honey (or maple syrup), sea salt, and freshly ground black pepper to make the dressing.",
      "Add the chopped broccoli, diced red onion, and dried cranberries to the bowl with the dressing. Toss to combine, ensuring all ingredients are evenly coated.",
      "Just before serving, fold in the cooled smoky almonds and pepitas, reserving a few for garnish.",
      "Season to taste with additional salt and pepper if needed. Serve immediately, or refrigerate for a few hours to allow the flavors to meld."
